[{"question":"What will I call you?","answer":"Your royal highness.","docId":"110220pmt","qSentId":2,"aSentId":3},{"question":"By what right?","answer":"By divine right if you must.","docId":"110220pmt","qSentId":24,"aSentId":25},{"question":"Why should I waste my time listening?","answer":"Because I have a right.","docId":"110220pmt","qSentId":30,"aSentId":31},{"question":"Do you think it is?","answer":"That will have to be for others to decide or for me to decide when I\u0027m so old that I\u0027m other -- it\u0027ll be in knotting away trying to grasp at any memories I have dictating my memoirs.","docId":"110220pmt","qSentId":42,"aSentId":43},{"question":"What did you think of Bertie, of King George VI?","answer":"I found the most -- I fell in love with him completely.","docId":"110220pmt","qSentId":50,"aSentId":51},{"question":"I\u0027ve actually heard some of the real footage of King George VI, and it\u0027s painful listening, isn\u0027t it?","answer":"It is.","docId":"110220pmt","qSentId":56,"aSentId":57},{"question":"When you\u0027re in the supermarket, and you\u0027re trying to order something, do you lapse into Bertie, just start stammering because you just got so used to that voice?","answer":"When I\u0027m in a supermarket, yes.","docId":"110220pmt","qSentId":69,"aSentId":70},{"question":"Aren\u0027t we both lucky?","answer":"Well, I thought I was lucky.","docId":"110220pmt","qSentId":90,"aSentId":91},{"question":"Do you quite like the fact of having been Darcy and having been in \"Bridget Jones\u0027\" stuff where you play the classic archetype of charmer that the last two great roles you\u0027ve had, \"Single Man\" and \"King\u0027s Speech,\" you\u0027re not actually playing that kind of character?","answer":"I do relish that.","docId":"110220pmt","qSentId":115,"aSentId":116},{"question":"You prefer it as an actor?","answer":"Of course.","docId":"110220pmt","qSentId":119,"aSentId":120},{"question":"But where does that leave you?","answer":"Leave me taking out the trash.","docId":"110220pmt","qSentId":157,"aSentId":158},{"question":"Is she amused by your sex symbol image?","answer":"Yes.","docId":"110220pmt","qSentId":160,"aSentId":161},{"question":"She\u0027s Italian, of course?","answer":"She\u0027s Italian.","docId":"110220pmt","qSentId":167,"aSentId":168},{"question":"How\u0027s your Italian?","answer":"(Speaking in foreign language)","docId":"110220pmt","qSentId":171,"aSentId":172},{"question":"Do you think all -- you know, do you find John Major sexy?","answer":"Not personally, no.","docId":"110220pmt","qSentId":182,"aSentId":183},{"question":"When we come back, what\u0027s the biggest turkey?","answer":"We don\u0027t go there.","docId":"110220pmt","qSentId":202,"aSentId":203},{"question":"Any kind of normality in that relationship?","answer":"IRTH: You know, I -- we\u0027ve made it 15 years together.","docId":"110220pmt","qSentId":241,"aSentId":242},{"question":"How do you avoid the shallow pitfalls of temptation like a thrown Hollywood heartthrob away?","answer":"It does help to actually realize that however stunning the person who\u0027s, you know, fluttering eyelashes at you is she doesn\u0027t do anything to match up to your wife.","docId":"110220pmt","qSentId":254,"aSentId":255},{"question":"And you don\u0027t really talk about them much, but as they get older, your children, would it unnerve you if they wanted to go into acting?","answer":"Oh, yes.","docId":"110220pmt","qSentId":270,"aSentId":271},{"question":"What would he have made of your success?","answer":"Well, he\u0027s still around.","docId":"110220pmt","qSentId":275,"aSentId":276},{"question":"Have I?","answer":"Apparently.","docId":"110220pmt","qSentId":287,"aSentId":288},{"question":"What\u0027s the biggest turkey?","answer":"We don\u0027t go there.","docId":"110220pmt","qSentId":291,"aSentId":292},{"question":"What\u0027s the worst?","answer":"We can\u0027t, you see.","docId":"110220pmt","qSentId":302,"aSentId":303},{"question":"Why not?","answer":"Because --","docId":"110220pmt","qSentId":304,"aSentId":305},{"question":"It\u0027s amazing, isn\u0027t it?","answer":"Spectacular.","docId":"110220pmt","qSentId":318,"aSentId":319},{"question":"Can I have all of them?","answer":"You can have two.","docId":"110220pmt","qSentId":321,"aSentId":322},{"question":"Do you like to do love scenes?","answer":"I like the idea of them.","docId":"110220pmt","qSentId":332,"aSentId":333},{"question":"Do you think no one would notice if you stepped in as a body double?","answer":"ORGAN: This is what I\u0027m thinking.","docId":"110220pmt","qSentId":337,"aSentId":338},{"question":"I mean can any wife enjoy watching their beloved husband romping with Scarlet Johansson?","answer":"I doubt it.","docId":"110220pmt","qSentId":362,"aSentId":363},{"question":"But if you were to introduce him yourself, how would you describe him?","answer":"I would describe him as my geisha girl.","docId":"110220pmt","qSentId":378,"aSentId":379},{"question":"Where is your hair?","answer":"Oh, I\u0027m doing a film about Humpty Dumpty down here.","docId":"110220pmt","qSentId":412,"aSentId":413},{"question":"How would you describe your relationship with Colin?","answer":"Well, we --","docId":"110220pmt","qSentId":418,"aSentId":419},{"question":"Do you believe in the royal family?","answer":"Oh.","docId":"110220pmt","qSentId":426,"aSentId":427},{"question":"Have you met any of them?","answer":"I have briefly met Prince Charles and I think he\u0027s a very, very interesting, very civil and civilized person.","docId":"110220pmt","qSentId":433,"aSentId":434},{"question":"Do you think the institution is a good one?","answer":"I like really voting.","docId":"110220pmt","qSentId":438,"aSentId":439},{"question":"Unelected institution isn\u0027t really your cup of tea?","answer":"It is a problem for me, yes.","docId":"110220pmt","qSentId":442,"aSentId":443},{"question":"Have you had a private bet between each other as to who may actually walk away with the old statue?","answer":"I\u0027ll let that one drift over to Australia.","docId":"110220pmt","qSentId":469,"aSentId":470},{"question":"Geoffrey?","answer":"I think Helena Bonham Carter will get it, and Colin and I won\u0027t, and will be furious.","docId":"110220pmt","qSentId":471,"aSentId":472},{"question":"Is it as nerve wrecking as I imagine it would be?","answer":"It\u0027s a post modernist experience I think, Piers.","docId":"110220pmt","qSentId":476,"aSentId":477},{"question":"What are you so afraid of?","answer":"Your poisonous words.","docId":"110220pmt","qSentId":493,"aSentId":494},{"question":"What was Colin like to work for, in terms of him working to you as a producer?","answer":"That -- that credit, I think, is more on the creative side.","docId":"110220pmt","qSentId":504,"aSentId":505},{"question":"How are you?","answer":"Very well.","docId":"110220pmt","qSentId":516,"aSentId":517},{"question":"How are you?","answer":"I\u0027m very well.","docId":"110220pmt","qSentId":518,"aSentId":519},{"question":"Did you ever meet the queen mother?","answer":"Yeah, I did, actually, when I was very, very young, a long, long time ago, at the premier of \"A Room With a View.","docId":"110220pmt","qSentId":521,"aSentId":522},{"question":"The two heavily-ego\u0027d movie stars?","answer":"They talk a lot.","docId":"110220pmt","qSentId":563,"aSentId":564},{"question":"Duke of York?","answer":"Yes, the Duke of York.","docId":"110220pmt","qSentId":615,"aSentId":616},{"question":"Am I considered the enemy?","answer":"You will be if you remain unobliging.","docId":"110220pmt","qSentId":622,"aSentId":623},{"question":"Have you, Geoffrey?","answer":"But then ask him.","docId":"110220pmt","qSentId":630,"aSentId":631},{"question":"What are your early thoughts, Helena?","answer":"Don\u0027t know.","docId":"110220pmt","qSentId":647,"aSentId":648},{"question":"But what are your views on Colin Firth the sex symbol?","answer":"I did fancy him in his uniform, with the medals.","docId":"110220pmt","qSentId":686,"aSentId":687},{"question":"Do you remember that?","answer":"Yes.","docId":"110220pmt","qSentId":688,"aSentId":689},{"question":"You like him as Darcy?","answer":"Yeah, yeah, I did, I did.","docId":"110220pmt","qSentId":690,"aSentId":691},{"question":"Would you fancy Piers in the same uniform?","answer":"No.","docId":"110220pmt","qSentId":702,"aSentId":703},{"question":"Wasn\u0027t it?","answer":"To see a woman come out who is a 48-year-old spinster in a tiny Scottish village, and everyone\u0027s laughing at here, and she\u0027s able to sing like Elaine Page, and we\u0027re all sniggering and everything else.","docId":"110220pmt","qSentId":724,"aSentId":725},{"question":"If Susan Boyle was here now Colin, singing \"I Dreamed a Dream,\" would you dream involve the Academy Awards end of February, standing there clutching the gong, making the speech you\u0027ve been preparing and practicing for probably 40 years?","answer":"You know, the thing that happens with this age -- this extraordinary advanced age I\u0027ve reached is that it\u0027s not the long-term memory going.","docId":"110220pmt","qSentId":732,"aSentId":733},{"question":"Is it the pinnacle?","answer":"I don\u0027t know how much one even really dares to contemplates dreams on that scale, really.","docId":"110220pmt","qSentId":744,"aSentId":745},{"question":"Can I chip in here?","answer":"IRTH: Yeah, go on, darling.","docId":"110220pmt","qSentId":752,"aSentId":753},{"question":"How could we forget?","answer":"He couldn\u0027t have been king without her.","docId":"110220pmt","qSentId":756,"aSentId":757}]